<dl id="n10052k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10052k">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10052k"> 52(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Brigit = Isolde / fostermother of JC</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">REMARKABLE DRAMA. PASSION PLAY AT THE ABBEY. Lady Gregory in the Passion Play, &ldquo;The Story Brought by Brigit,&rdquo; which had its first production before a large audience in the Abbey Theatre last night, makes used of a pretty and interesting tradition that <mark>St. Brigit was the foster-mother of Christ</mark>&mdash;the Mary of the Gael. <small> <a name="II16apr24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#II16apr24"><cite title="source">Irish Independent</cite></a> (16 April 1924) 6/4</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
